[2026-03-13T20:04:01Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01HjMkovk1RuozHnFnZS9pvt","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed to provide a comprehensive report. Let me compile the findings:\n\n## Comprehensive Web UI Log Display Exploration Report\n\nBased on my thorough codebase exploration, here's a complete map of all files and mechanisms related to web UI log display for runs:\n\n### 1. **Web Handler Files** (HTTP/HTML Layer)\n- **Primary handler**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (1,895 lines)\n  - Main orchestrator for all web dashboard routes and API endpoints\n  - Imports `logstream` package for log parsing and broadcasting\n  - Contains 16+ API handler methods\n\n### 2. **HTML Templates** (Template Layer)\nLocated in `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/`:\n- `layout.html` - Base template layout with navbar and main content structure\n- `run_detail.html` - Individual run detail page (356 lines) with embedded JavaScript for:\n  - SSE (Server-Sent Events) stream connection: `GET /api/runs/{id}/stream`\n  - Step-by-step log display with collapsible accordion UI\n  - Real-time polling for container status and step updates\n  - Step output fetching via `/api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output`\n- `runs.html` - Runs list page (164 lines) with polling at 3-second intervals\n- `projects.html` - Projects overview (576 lines) with workflow DAG rendering\n- `project_detail.html` - Project detail page (193 lines)\n\n### 3. **Static Assets**\n- `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` (617 lines)\n  - CSS for log viewer: `.log-viewer`, `.log-line`, `.log-type-*` classes\n  - Max height: 600px with auto-scroll\n  - Color-coded log types: status (blue), llm (green), script (default)\n\n### 4. **gRPC API & Streaming** (API Layer)\n\n**Proto definitions** (`/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto`):\n- `StreamLogs(StreamLogsRequest) returns (stream LogEntry)`\n  - Parameters:\n    - `run_id`: Target run\n    - `step_name`: Optional filter by step\n    - `log_type`: Optional filter (script/llm)\n    - `follow`: Boolean flag for tail -f behavior (via gRPC metadata: `x-cloche-follow`)\n  \n- `LogEntry` message structure:\n  - `type`: Log entry type (status, script, llm, full_log, run_completed, etc.)\n  - `step_name`: Originating step name\n  - `result`: Step execution result\n  - `message`: Log content\n  - `timestamp`: RFC3339 formatted timestamp\n\n**gRPC Server implementation** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go`):\n- `StreamLogs()` method (lines 487-596)\n  - Checks for follow mode via context metadata\n  - Routes to different handlers:\n    - `streamFilteredLogs()` - For step/log_type filters\n    - `streamFollowLogs()` - For active runs with -f flag (snapshot + tail)\n  - Falls back to full.log or captures if available\n  - No pagination; streams entire log sequentially\n\n- `streamFollowLogs()` (lines 610-656)\n  - Subscribe-first pattern to avoid race conditions\n  - Reads existing full.log then tails live output from broadcaster\n  - Sends \"full_log\" message followed by live \"log\" messages\n\n- `streamFilteredLogs()` (lines 658-726)\n  - Uses LogStore index when available for fast lookups\n  - Falls back to file path conventions (step.log, llm-step.log, etc.)\n  - Single stream.Send() per log file\n\n### 5. **Log Store Interface** (`/workspace/internal/ports/store.go`)\n\n**CaptureStore interface**:\n```go\nSaveCapture(ctx context.Context, runID string, exec *domain.StepExecution) error\nGetCaptures(ctx context.Context, runID string) ([]*domain.StepExecution, error)\n```\n\n**LogStore interface**:\n```go\nSaveLogFile(ctx context.Context, entry *LogFileEntry) error\nGetLogFiles(ctx context.Context, runID string) ([]*LogFileEntry, error)\nGetLogFilesByStep(ctx context.Context, runID, stepName string) ([]*LogFileEntry, error)\nGetLogFileByType(ctx context.Context, runID, fileType string) ([]*LogFileEntry, error)\n```\n\n### 6. **SQLite Store Implementation** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go`)\n\n**LogStore methods** (lines 343-384):\n- `SaveLogFile()` - Indexes log files with (run_id, step_name, file_type, file_path)\n- `GetLogFiles()` - Retrieves all log files for a run\n- `GetLogFilesByStep()` - Fast lookup by (run_id, step_name)\n- `GetLogFileByType()` - Filter by file type (full, script, llm)\n- `scanLogFiles()` - Scanner for parsing results\n\n**Database schema** (log_files table):\n- id, run_id, step_name, file_type, file_path, file_size, created_at\n\n### 7. **Log Streaming & Broadcasting** (`/workspace/internal/logstream/`)\n\n**Broadcaster** (`broadcaster.go`):\n- Thread-safe pub/sub for active runs\n- `Subscribe(runID)` - Returns channel for log lines\n- `Publish(runID, LogLine)` - Broadcasts to all subscribers\n- `Finish(runID)` - Marks run complete, closes all channels\n- Non-blocking publish with drop-on-slow-subscriber\n\n**Writer** (`logstream.go`):\n- Writes timestamped log entries to `/workspace/.cloche/{runID}/output/full.log`\n- Format: `[RFC3339] [type] content`\n- Types: \"status\", \"script\", \"llm\"\n- Thread-safe with sync.Mutex\n\n**Parser** (`parse.go`):\n- `ParseClaudeLine([]byte)` - Parses single Claude Code stream-json line\n- `ParseClaudeStream([]byte)` - Converts raw Claude stream-json to human-readable text\n- Extracts assistant text, tool calls, error messages\n- Handles both Claude Code and Streaming API formats\n- Returns empty type for protocol-only events\n\n### 8. **HTTP Handler Methods** (Web Layer - handler.go)\n\n**HTML handlers**:\n- `handleProjectOverview()` - Landing page with project cards\n- `handleRunsList()` - List all runs or filter by project\n- `handleRunDetail()` - Single run detail page (HTML)\n- `handleProjectDetail()` - Project detail page\n- `renderRunsList()` - Helper for runs list rendering\n\n**API handlers** (JSON responses):\n- `handleAPIRuns()` - List runs (filtered, grouped by task)\n- `handleAPIProjectRuns()` - List runs for a project\n- `handleAPIRunDetail()` - Run detail with steps\n- `handleAPIStepOutput()` - Get output for single step (lines 807-871)\n  - Query params: `type` (script/llm), `format` (raw to skip parsing)\n  - Priority: LogStore index → file path conventions\n  - Reads from per-step .log files\n  - Skips container.log to avoid mismatches\n  - Parses Claude JSON if format != raw\n- `handleAPIStream()` - SSE stream for live logs (lines 1064-1127)\n  - Completed runs: Serves full.log as SSE events\n  - Active runs: Subscribes to broadcaster\n  - Parses full.log line-by-line with regex\n  - Supports LLM log line parsing\n- Other: stop, delete container, project info, workflows, tasks\n\n**SSE (Server-Sent Events) implementation** (`handleAPIStream`):\n- Content-Type: text/event-stream\n- No caching (Cache-Control: no-cache)\n- Keep-alive for active runs\n- JSON-encoded LogLine messages\n- Terminal \"done\" event with run state\n- HTTP Flusher for immediate delivery\n\n### 9. **Frontend JavaScript** (Embedded in Templates)\n\n**In run_detail.html** (lines 108-354):\n- EventSource for SSE: `/api/runs/{runID}/stream`\n- Real-time log appending with auto-scroll\n- Smart scroll position preservation\n- Status badge: \"Live\" → \"Complete\"\n- Polling for step updates every 2 seconds\n- Accordion UI for step outputs\n- Step output fetching on expand: `/api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output`\n- Container status polling\n\n**In runs.html** (lines 99-160):\n- Polling loop every 3 seconds\n- Project filter with dynamic URL navigation\n- Container cleanup button with count update\n\n**In project_detail.html** (lines 54-575):\n- Workflow DAG rendering with SVG\n- Task pipeline status display\n- Prompt diff viewing\n- Step content drawer\n- 5-second task status polling\n\n### 10. **Test Coverage** (`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_stream_test.go`)\n- SSE completion test: `TestSSE_CompletedRun_ServesFullLog()`\n- Verifies full.log parsing and SSE event generation\n- Tests log line JSON unmarshaling\n\n### 11. **Key Data Flow Paths**\n\n**For completed runs**:\n```\nHTTP GET /api/runs/{id}/stream\n  → handler.go:handleAPIStream()\n  → read .cloche/{id}/output/full.log\n  → parseFullLogLine() + parseLLMLogLine()\n  → SSE data events\n```\n\n**For active runs**:\n```\nAgent publishes to broadcaster\n  → Broadcaster.Publish(runID, LogLine)\n  → handleAPIStream() receives via sub.C\n  → SSE data events\n  → On completion: Broadcaster.Finish() → done event\n```\n\n**For step-specific output**:\n```\nHTTP GET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output?type=llm\n  → handleAPIStepOutput()\n  → LogStore.GetLogFilesByStep() OR file system fallback\n  → ParseClaudeStream() if type is \"llm\"\n  → Plain text response\n```\n\n### 12. **Key Files Summary**\n\n| File | Purpose | Key Components |\n|------|---------|-----------------|\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` | HTTP handlers & routing | 16+ API endpoints, template rendering |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` | Run UI | SSE, log display, step accordion |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/grpc/server.go` | gRPC streaming | StreamLogs, follow mode, filtering |\n| `/workspace/internal/logstream/broadcaster.go` | Live streaming | Pub/sub for active runs |\n| `/workspace/internal/logstream/logstream.go` | Log writing | Full.log writer with timestamps |\n| `/workspace/internal/logstream/parse.go` | Log parsing | Claude stream-json parsing |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/sqlite/store.go` | Log indexing | LogStore impl, log_files table |\n| `/workspace/internal/ports/store.go` | Interfaces | LogStore, CaptureStore definitions |\n| `/workspace/api/proto/cloche/v1/cloche.proto` | gRPC schema | StreamLogs RPC definition |\n| `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` | Styling | Log viewer CSS |\n\n### 13. **Pagination/Streaming Strategy**\n- **No explicit pagination**: Streams entire logs sequentially\n- **Memory management**: Large logs (1MB+) handled with 256KB+ buffer in scanner\n- **Live streaming**: Non-blocking publish with drop-on-full-subscriber\n- **Follow mode**: Combines snapshot + tail for continuity (like `tail -f`)\n\nThis architecture provides real-time log display with optional filtering, supporting both HTML/SSE and gRPC streaming protocols."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a2164d8d02f6ed067 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 78744\ntool_uses: 38\nduration_ms: 63952</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"143fc353-8adb-4cb0-8d24-a68ddf79996d","uuid":"6baa30f8-84b0-4e8d-bcf9-6b5927a84016","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the codebase to find all files related to the web UI log display for runs. I need to understand:\n\n1. Where the web UI is served from (handlers, templates, static files)\n2. How logs are fetched and displayed for individual runs\n3. Any existing pagination or streaming logic for logs\n4. The gRPC or HTTP API endpoints that serve log data\n5. How the CaptureStore/log store works\n\nLook for:\n- Web handler files (likely in internal/adapters/)\n- HTML templates for log views\n- JavaScript files for log display\n- gRPC proto definitions related to logs\n- CaptureStore interface and implementations\n\nBe very thorough - search for patterns like \"log\", \"capture\", \"web\", \"handler\", \"template\", \"html\", \"follow\", \"stream\" across the codebase.","agentId":"a2164d8d02f6ed067","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Perfect! Now I have all the information needed to provide a comprehensive report. Let me compile the findings:\n\n## Comprehensive Web UI Log Display Exploration Report\n\nBased on my thorough codebase exploration, here's a complete map of all files and mechanisms related to web UI log display for runs:\n\n### 1. **Web Handler Files** (HTTP/HTML Layer)\n- **Primary handler**: `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (1,895 lines)\n  - M