[2026-03-13T20:06:01Z] [llm] {"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01FW1G2xTb2zHJawU3KSSB6C","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Let me create a comprehensive summary report of my findings:\n\n## Summary: Web UI Log Display - Current State\n\nI've thoroughly explored the web UI code related to log display. Here are my findings:\n\n### 1. **1000 Line Limit - Core Implementation**\n\n**Reference:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` line 1063\n\n```go\nconst defaultLogTail = 1000\n```\n\nThis constant defines the **maximum number of log lines sent on initial page load** for completed runs. The behavior:\n- When a completed run's logs exceed 1000 lines, only the last 1000 are initially streamed\n- The earlier lines are made available for \"load more\" functionality\n- An SSE \"meta\" event is sent first with `total_lines` and `skipped` counts\n\n### 2. **SSE Stream Endpoint: `/api/runs/{id}/stream`**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 1065-1133)\n\n**Behavior:**\n- For **completed runs**: calls `streamFullLog(w, flusher, run, defaultLogTail)` which:\n  - Reads the archived `full.log` file\n  - Parses and filters LLM lines into human-readable text\n  - Caps output to last 1000 lines\n  - Sends metadata event if lines were skipped\n  - Streams remaining lines as SSE events\n- For **active runs**: subscribes to live broadcaster for real-time log streaming\n\n**Key Changes Made:**\n- Modified `streamFullLog` signature to accept a `tail int` parameter\n- Added metadata event emission with `{\"total_lines\": N, \"skipped\": M}` when earlier lines are skipped (lines 1232-1236)\n\n### 3. **Pagination API Endpoint: `/api/runs/{id}/logs`**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` (lines 1135-1186)\n\n**New endpoint** for loading earlier log lines on demand.\n\n**Query parameters:**\n- `end`: exclusive upper bound (visible line index); defaults to total lines\n- `limit`: max lines to return; defaults to `defaultLogTail` (1000)\n\n**Response:**\n```json\n{\n  \"lines\": [...],\n  \"total\": N,\n  \"start\": S,\n  \"end\": E\n}\n```\n\n**Implementation logic:**\n- Reads all visible log lines from full.log\n- Calculates `start = end - limit`\n- Clamps `start` to 0 if negative (first page handling)\n- Returns the slice `lines[start:end]`\n\n### 4. **UI Components - \"Load Earlier\" Button**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html`\n\n**Button UI (lines 105-108):**\n```html\n<button id=\"load-earlier-btn\" class=\"load-earlier-btn\" style=\"display:none\" \n    onclick=\"loadEarlierLogs()\">\n    Load earlier (<span id=\"load-earlier-count\">0</span> more lines)\n</button>\n```\n\n**Visibility logic:**\n- Button initially hidden\n- Becomes visible when SSE meta event is received with `skipped > 0`\n- Updates count dynamically as user loads more lines\n\n**JavaScript Implementation (lines 305-349):**\n- `loadEarlierLogs()` function fetches from `/api/runs/{id}/logs?end={skippedLines}&limit=1000`\n- Creates document fragments for better performance\n- Inserts loaded lines at top of log viewer (preserving scroll position)\n- Updates `skippedLines` tracker from response\n- Hides button when all earlier lines are loaded (`skippedLines = 0`)\n\n**Scroll Preservation Logic (lines 327-330):**\n```javascript\nvar prevScrollHeight = logViewer.scrollHeight;\nlogContent.insertBefore(fragment, logContent.firstChild);\nlogViewer.scrollTop += logViewer.scrollHeight - prevScrollHeight;\n```\n\n### 5. **SSE Meta Event Handling**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html` (lines 158-167)\n\nThe template registers a listener for the \"meta\" SSE event:\n```javascript\nsource.addEventListener('meta', function(e) {\n    var meta = JSON.parse(e.data);\n    skippedLines = meta.skipped || 0;\n    if (skippedLines > 0) {\n        loadEarlierCount.textContent = skippedLines;\n        loadEarlierBtn.style.display = '';\n    }\n});\n```\n\n### 6. **Log Filtering and Parsing**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`\n\n**New helper function** (lines 1189-1212):\n- `readVisibleLogLines(logPath)` - reads full.log and returns parsed, filtered log lines\n- Filters out protocol-only LLM events (empty type)\n- Handles large JSON lines (up to 1MB with 256KB buffer)\n\n**Parsing logic:**\n- `parseFullLogLine` - parses `[timestamp] [type] content` format\n- `parseLLMLogLine` - extracts human-readable text from Claude JSON\n\n### 7. **CSS Styling**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css` (lines 407-423)\n\nNew `.load-earlier-btn` styles:\n```css\n.load-earlier-btn {\n    display: block;\n    width: 100%;\n    padding: 0.4rem;\n    background: var(--bg-secondary);\n    border: none;\n    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);\n    cursor: pointer;\n    color: var(--link);\n}\n.load-earlier-btn:hover { background: var(--border); }\n.load-earlier-btn:disabled { opacity: 0.5; cursor: wait; }\n```\n\n### 8. **Test Coverage**\n\n**File:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_stream_test.go`\n\nNew comprehensive tests added:\n- `TestSSE_CompletedRun_TailsLast1000` - verifies 1000-line limit with meta event\n- `TestSSE_CompletedRun_NoMetaWhenUnderLimit` - verifies no meta event when under 1000 lines\n- `TestAPILogs_Pagination` - tests pagination endpoint with default limit\n- `TestAPILogs_PaginateEarlier` - tests loading earlier pages\n- `TestAPILogs_FirstPage` - tests first page clamping\n- `TestAPILogs_RunNotFound` - tests error handling\n- `TestAPILogs_NoLogFile` - tests empty log handling\n- Helper function `writeNLogLines` - generates test log files\n\n### Key Files Modified:\n\n1. **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go`** - Main handler implementation\n2. **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/templates/run_detail.html`** - UI template and JavaScript\n3. **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/static/style.css`** - Styling for load button\n4. **`/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler_stream_test.go`** - Test coverage for new features\n\n### Architecture Overview:\n\n```\nCompleted Run (large logs)\n    ↓\nSSE /stream endpoint\n    ↓\nTail 1000 lines + meta event → Browser\n    ↓\nDisplay 1000 lines + \"Load earlier\" button\n    ↓\nUser clicks button\n    ↓\nFetch /api/logs?end=X&limit=1000\n    ↓\nInsert at top, preserve scroll position\n    ↓\nUpdate button count or hide if all loaded\n```"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a3b8c541400fcce49 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 60507\ntool_uses: 20\nduration_ms: 40227</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"8530080f-5bbb-4b36-9913-140e127b35d2","uuid":"0f25cdbf-9d9c-41f8-a7b1-c940cda9f0d3","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Explore the current state of the web UI code related to log display, particularly:\n1. The handler.go file for any log-related endpoints, especially pagination or line limits\n2. The run_detail.html template for log display UI\n3. The handler_stream_test.go for streaming test changes\n4. The style.css for any new styles\n5. Any documentation files about the web UI\n\nFocus on finding:\n- Any \"1000\" line limit references\n- \"load more\" or \"load-previous\" button implementations\n- Log pagination parameters (offset, limit, etc.)\n- SSE/streaming endpoints for logs\n\nSearch thoroughly in internal/adapters/web/ and docs/","agentId":"a3b8c541400fcce49","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Let me create a comprehensive summary report of my findings:\n\n## Summary: Web UI Log Display - Current State\n\nI've thoroughly explored the web UI code related to log display. Here are my findings:\n\n### 1. **1000 Line Limit - Core Implementation**\n\n**Reference:** `/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go` line 1063\n\n```go\nconst defaultLogTail = 1000\n```\n\nThis constant defines the **maximum number of log lines sent on initi